
Commit Message

Subject: Refactor: Major structural upgrade for GUI support and Standard Library migration

Description:
This commit implements a fundamental shift in the Luna language architecture to support high-level graphical features and an immediate-mode GUI system.

Key Changes:

    Language Core & Native Bridge:

        Updated NativeFunc signature to include Env* for real-time environment variable binding.

        Implemented "Auto-Main" execution logic in main.c to support event loops.

    Standard Library Migration:

        Systematically updated all built-in libraries (math, string, file, vec, list, time) to match the new 3-argument native signature.

    GUI & Media Engine (gui/):

        Introduced a dedicated gui/ directory for modular graphics logic.

        Integrated Raylib for rendering, including support for windowing and transparency.

        Added Resource Managers for Font and Texture caching using an ID-based handle system.

        Implemented high-quality text rendering with Bilinear Filtering support for TTF fonts.

    New Native Features:

        Visuals: draw_rect, draw_circle, load_texture, draw_texture, load_font, draw_text.

        Input: Added is_key_down and gui_get_mouse for interactive control.

        Widgets: Added gui_slider with stateful variable binding and auto-layout buttons/labels.

    Build System:

        Updated Makefile to include the gui/ folder, manage Raylib dependencies, and support static linking.

